{"questionId":"27002767","questionHtml":"<p>The following diagram shows part of the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"__IMG__/2ebe7721ad0e0f3fe404a2e2229e48f994469b16.png\"></p>\n<p>The shaded region <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is bounded by the curve, the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis and the line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>The area of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>3</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>=</mo><munderover><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mi>c</mi></munderover><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to integrate by inspection or substitution using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If candidate simply states <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, but does not attempt to integrate, do not award the <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em>.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> If candidate does not explicitly state the u-substitution, award the <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> only for expressions of the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>u</mi></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>u</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>u</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn><mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi>u</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>0</mn><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msubsup></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>0</mn><mi>c</mi></msubsup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Limits may be seen in the substitution step.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to integrate by inspection&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award the <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> only for expressions of the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfenced><mn>0</mn><mi>c</mi></msubsup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Limits may be seen in the substitution step.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>correctly substitutes their limits into their integrated expression&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>(</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p>correctly applies at least one log law to their expression&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><msqrt><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>9</mn></math></p>\n<p><strong>OR&nbsp;</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>9</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt></mfrac></msqrt><mo>(</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone the absence of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>3</mn></math> up to this stage.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>c</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>16</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A0</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><mn>4</mn></math> as a final answer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27002767","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ2.5","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"The following diagram shows part of the graph of y=xx2+2 for x≥0. The shaded region R is bounded by the curve, the x-axis and the line x=c. The area of R is ln 3. Find the value of","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"5","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.10—Indefinite integration, reverse chain, by substitution","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.11—Definite integrals, areas under curve onto x-axis and areas between curves","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.10—Solving equations graphically and analytically","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.7—Laws of exponents and logs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}